Ivanhoe was first listed as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusVA/>

According to the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], the CDP had a total population of 551, of whom 97.10% were White, 1.45% were American Indian or Alaska Native, 0.91 were some other race, 0.18% were two or more races. Of these, 1.45% were Hispanic or Latino of any race.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://censusviewer.com/city/VA/ivanhoe/2010|title=2010 Census Population of Ivanhoe, Virginia|last=|first=|date=|website=CensusViewer|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171020140218/http://censusviewer.com/city/VA/ivanhoe/2010|url-status=usurped|archive-date=October 20, 2017|access-date=2018-03-21}}</ref>

